-- Argentine Stocks: Grupo Financiero Galicia, Ledesma and Tenaris
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-01-05T20:29:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-05/argentine-stocks-grupo-financiero-galicia-ledesma-and-tenaris.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the close in Buenos
Aires.  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index closed little changed at 2,715.19.  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL AF) advanced 0.9 percent
to 3.45 pesos. Argentina’s largest consumer lender has increased
25 percent in the past four sessions, the largest four-day gain
since May 2009, after its weighting in the Merval benchmark
index increased to 22 percent from 13 percent.  Tenaris SA (TEN)   fell 2.4 percent to 91.75 pesos. The
world’s largest producer of seamless steel tubes used in the oil
industry fell in line with the price of crude in New York.  Ledesma SA (LEDE)   dropped 3.5 percent to 7.24 pesos, the
biggest decline in a week. The Argentine food company fell after
the head of  Argentina ’s corn growers association said that the
La Nina weather pattern is causing a “much worse” drought than
expected.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
